Ad Text:
The purpose of the Senior Digital Tag Management Analyst role is to lead and implement good practice in the digital data instrumentation of enterprise HCF digital estate.

Key Responsibilities

Architect and Develop Scalable Digital Analytics Solutions: Lead the design and implementation of scalable digital analytics solutions, ensuring alignment with the enterprise's digital analytics architecture.

Drive Strategic Data Initiatives: Lead strategic initiatives to enhance digital data capabilities, ensuring alignment with broader business goals and objectives.

Innovate Advanced Tagging Solutions: Identify and implement cutting-edge tagging solutions to future-proof digital data collection capabilities.

Oversee Digital Data Collection and Tagging: Manage and maintain the digital data collection and tagging of HCF digital assets, delivering a best-in-class data layer that supports market-leading identity management, reporting, and segmentation capabilities.

Define and Implement Digital Data Layer Requirements: Collaborate with the developer community to define digital data layer requirements, oversee tag implementation, and support comprehensive testing phases including data validation dashboards.

Ensure Data Integrity and Operational Efficiency: Troubleshoot and resolve issues related to tagging and data collection, performing regular data validation checks to maintain data integrity and ensure smooth operations.

Centralize Digital Data Tagging Documentation: Create and maintain a central repository of digital data tagging requirements and solution design documents.

Optimize Tag Implementation Governance: Develop and optimize frameworks to enhance tag implementation governance practices, continuously contributing to the practice's evolution.

Collaborate Across Business Units: Partner with enterprise digital, marketing, technology, and other business units to expand digital data coverage across the enterprise.

Govern Digital Data Pipelines: Establish and govern digital data pipelines with the enterprise customer data platform (Adobe RT CDP) to enrich customer profiles for experimentation and personalization.

Identify and Address Insight Needs: Work with Digital Teams to identify insight needs, agree on digital data sets, and define requirements for KPI monitoring and digital optimization.

Provide Technical Expertise in A/B Testing and Optimization: Offer technical support and strategic advice in A/B testing and insights-driven optimization for website performance via Adobe Target, while maintaining tag management and data validity across HCF.

Stay Ahead of Industry Trends: Keep abreast of the latest trends and advancements in digital analytics and data collection technologies, ensuring the organization remains at the forefront of the industry.

Enhance Customer Experience: Utilize digital analytics to drive improvements in customer experience, leveraging data insights to inform strategic decisions and optimize digital touchpoints

Essential Skills

Bachelor's degree in Marketing, Engineering, Data Science, or a related field.

4+ years of experience in a similar role with experience in Digital data collection and tag implementation and running multivariate test for insight-based optimisation

Proven experience in managing large-scale digital analytics projects.

Strong understanding of digital analytics tools and platforms (e.g., Adobe Analytics, Google Analytics).

Strong understanding of tag management data layer

Working knowledge with JavaScript

Experience working directly with developers in implementing analytic solutions

Experience within an optimisation program aimed at improving onsite conversion

Experience in online marketing campaigns, across channels including SEO, SEM, Display and Social.

Adobe Analytics and Target extensive experience (preferable)

A generative mindset. You come from a place of possibility, think on your feet and outside the square and adapt well to change.

DESIRABLE

Tertiary qualifications in Business or Marketing (desirable) or other relevant qualification.

Experience in customer data platforms such as AEP to contribute in the website personalisation activities is desirable

About HCF

At HCF, our purpose is to bring our human touch to healthcare. Since 1932 we've been putting our members and their health first. As Australia's largest not-for-profit health fund, we cover over 1.9 million members with health, life, travel and pet insurance and our vision is to make healthcare understandable, affordable, high quality and member centric.

We want to be true health partners to our members, easily guiding the healthcare choices that are right for them. At HCF, our values are the way we do things and create the necessary culture to help us realise our purpose and deliver our Strategy. Living our values in action we step forward, walk in their shoes, stay human, make it better and get there together.

Culture & Benefits

Purpose-driven passion
We're united by a common purpose: to make healthcare affordable, understandable, high quality and member-focused.

Wellness and work-life balance
We'll empower you with the necessary skills and tools to support your personal wellbeing journey, ensuring you perform at your best. Our offerings include:
* 50% subsidy on HCF hospital and/or extras cover
* 18 weeks of parental leave for all new parents
* Mental health and wellbeing programs, including workshops, fitness classes, flu vaccinations, skin checks and more
* Discounts on HCF's products, including life, pet and travel Insurance, as well as discounts at Fitness First gyms and on our eyecare products.

Collaboration and inclusivity
We embrace diversity as our strength and are committed to maintaining an inclusive and collaborative work environment. Our workplace is welcoming and safe for all our employees, irrespective of their unique characteristics including age, ethnicity, cultural or spiritual background, gender identity, disability, education and socio-economic status.

Continuous learning and growth
We believe in lifelong learning. HCF provides opportunities for personal and professional development. From workshops to mentorship programs, we encourage your growth and curiosity.



Next steps

If you require any adjustments to assist you in making your application or during the recruitment or onboarding process, please reach out to Talent Acquisition - peopleservices@hcf.com.au to discuss.

We encourage applicants to submit their applications at their earliest convenience, as at HCF, we review applications as they are submitted, and may have filled the role prior to the job closing date.

Job Title: Head of City Insights and Analytics
Category:
Management (Information & Communication Technology)
Government - Local (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
About the role

We are seeking a dynamic leader to head the City Insights and Analytics function. As the Head of City Insights and Analytics you will combine strategic vision and technical expertise to deliver high-quality data and insights that drive evidence-based decisions across the City of Melbourne and our community. You will lead a talented team in developing and maintaining data products, tools, and consulting solutions, while building strategic partnerships internally and externally. Highly collaborative and influential, this role offers the opportunity to shape organisational impact and contribute to the city’s future.

The position will require you too

Set and deliver the City Insights and Analytics strategy, operating model and roadmap to ensure CoM remains a leader in advanced analytics, applied AI and decision intelligence.

Prioritise analytics initiatives to align with organisational strategy and deliver the greatest strategic, operational and community impact.

Act as a trusted strategic partner to senior leaders, using consulting and problem-framing approaches to define insight needs, drive service excellence and inform major strategies, investments and city initiatives.

Lead the development and application of advanced analytics, forecasting, evaluation, scenario modelling, AI and automation to improve decision quality, performance, risk mitigation and resource allocation.

Ensure the highest standards of data governance, analytical rigour and methodological integrity across all insights and products.

Translate complex analysis into clear, compelling data stories and narratives that connect evidence to strategic decisions, outcomes and trade-offs for executives, Council, external stakeholders and the media using dashboards, visualisations, performance indicators and briefings.

Ensure insights are communicated effectively and presented with narrative clarity, so stakeholders can quickly understand the “so what”, the risks, and the actions required.

Uplift data literacy and evidence-based decision making across the organisation through role modelling, self-service tools and knowledge sharing.

Partner with digital and technology teams to deliver scalable, secure and user-centred analytics platforms and data products.

Build and maintaining strong internal and external partnerships across government, industry, academia and the community to enhance impact, innovation and build CoM’s reputation as a leading Smart City.

Contributing to enterprise planning, governance, audit, reporting and budget processes, and supporting the Director, Enterprise Planning and Insights in achieving branch and organisational objectives.

Why join Team Melbourne?

Located on the traditional lands of the Bunurong Boon Wurrung and Wurundjeri Woi-wurrung peoples of the Kulin Nation, Melbourne is globally recognised as one of the most liveable, diverse, and dynamic cities.

At the heart of it all is the City of Melbourne – a passionate, purpose-driven organisation where your work truly matters. As part of Team Melbourne, you’ll help deliver what’s most important to the people who live, work, study, visit and invest in our great city.

We’re proud champions of diversity, committed to continuous improvement, and driven by a shared vision for a vibrant and sustainable future.

This is more than just a role, it’s your chance to make a real impact, contribute to something bigger, and shape Melbourne’s future alongside a collaborative and forward-thinking team.

What your experience might look like

Experience as an established people leader with experience leading teams through change

Relevant tertiary qualification in ICT, data science, mathematics, economics, or equivalent professional experience in data analytics.

Proven experience building and leading data science and analytics teams that deliver business value.

Proficient in data analysis and tools, including PowerBI, Databricks, SharePoint, Excel, SQL, R Shiny, GIS, and Azure.

Experience with cloud and on-premise data environments.

Skilled in creating and maintaining insightful, story-driven dashboards using various visualization tools.

Familiarity with emerging digital and technology platforms, including AR/VR and engagement tools.

Experience in agile project management and collaborating effectively across cross-functional teams.

Strong organisational skills, able to manage competing priorities with attention to detail and accuracy.

Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with the ability to develop creative solutions.

Experienced in building and nurturing partnerships within complex environments.

Strong written and oral communication skills, with the ability to engage and influence internal and external stakeholders.

Benefits of working with us

Attractive remuneration & benefits: Excellent pay package with a range of exciting benefits. Flexible working, study assistance & other great corporate discounts.

Excellent leave entitlements: Enjoy up to 20 weeks of fully paid parental leave for primary carers, in addition to the government-funded parental leave, with no waiting period to access. Part-time equivalents are also available for added flexibility.

Career progression: Career development support and opportunities to learn new skills within a creative and exciting environment.

Work-life balance and hybrid working: We support flexible hours, alternative work arrangements (like ADOs), and hybrid work-from-home options.

How to apply

We would love to hear how you can make an impact in this role! As part of your application, you will be required to:

Attach your updated resume

Include a cover letter (max one page) outlining your relevant experience and why you're a great fit for this role.

Submit your application no later than 11:45pm on 17 February 2026.

A few important things to note – don’t miss out!

Applications must be submitted online. Unfortunately, we can’t accept applications via email, so please be sure to apply through the official job link provided.

Apply early! This role may close sooner than the listed closing date if we find the right candidate — so don’t wait to get your application in.

We are a child safe organisation. The City of Melbourne has a zero tolerance for child abuse. All employees undergo thorough safety screening, including a Police Check and, for most roles, a Working with Children Check.

Need more info?

Refer to the position description below or contact Justin Randle - Director Enterprise Planning and Insights at justin.randle@melbourne.vic.gov.au

Inclusion matters

We strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, people from all cultural and linguistic backgrounds, people with disabilities, LGBTIQA+ individuals, and people of all ages and faith backgrounds.

We provide reasonable adjustments throughout the recruitment process to support all applicants. If you require any adjustments, please let us know via the application prompts or inform our Careers team if you’re contacted for an interview.

Job Title: Senior Business Improvement and Change Manager
Ad Text:
Senior Business Improvement and Change Manager

Fixed term, full time, 12 months with possible extension.

West Leederville

Over the last 70 years Relationships Australia WA has been providing relationship support services for individuals, couples, families and communities. We are a team of professional and highly motivated staff who are committed to enhancing the lives of communities, families and individuals and supporting positive and respectful relationships.

About the role

We are seeking a Senior Business Improvement and Change Manager to join our West Leederville Corporate office for a fixed term. Play a pivotal role in ensuring the success of our digital transformation by optimising service delivery processes and leading organisational change for over 300 staff and 15,000+ clients. This role bridges technical implementation and operational adoption within an Agile Scrum team. The current vacancy is 37.5 hours per week.

Skills, experience, and qualifications

Core Responsibilities

Business Improvement & Process Optimisation

Map current state processes and collaboratively design future state workflows that leverage new technology.

Enlist and enable internal business improvement champions to drive process optimisation across locations.

Change Management

Design and execute comprehensive change management strategies, including stakeholder analysis, impact assessments, and readiness plans.

Develop targeted communications and engagement activities to build awareness and knowledge across the staff base.

Evidence-Based Decision Making

Utilise evidence-based management frameworks to measure value, identify gaps, and validate improvements.

Monitor adoption metrics post-release and iterate on support mechanisms to ensure sustained change.

Training & Capability

Define training requirements and oversee the creation of support materials to ensure staff proficiency with new systems.

Team & Culture Contributions

Operate as a core member of the Scrum team, integrating change management and process improvement into the development lifecycle.

Champion agile practices and foster an environment of psychological safety, creativity, and experimentation.

Support consensus-based decisions grounded in evidence and expertise.

Uphold organisational values: Authenticity, Inclusivity, Compassion, and Excellence.

Qualifications and Experience:

Tertiary qualifications in Business, IT, Organisational Psychology, or related discipline, or equivalent professional experience.

Minimum 5 years’ experience in Business Improvement or Change Management roles within technology transformation projects.

Demonstrated experience working effectively within Agile/Scrum delivery teams.

Key Selection Criteria - Knowledge:

Deep understanding of change management principles (PROSCI/ADKAR highly regarded).

Strong knowledge of process improvement methodologies (Lean Six Sigma highly regarded).

Working knowledge of Agile/Scrum and evidence-based management.

Key Selection Criteria - Skills and Experience:

Proven ability to work autonomously and take ownership of change strategy.

Strong analytical skills and ability to use data/evidence to drive decisions.

Exceptional interpersonal skills and ability to influence stakeholders at all levels.

Other Requirements:

A current Working with Children Check and WA Police Force National Police Check to obtain upon required)

Application instructions:

Applications must include a cover letter outlining suitability for the role, the area you are located closest to, and a current resume citing professional referees and to be submitted via SEEK.

Applications close at 4pm, 21 January 2026

As Senior Engineer - Data and Business Intelligence of our Data Analytics Services team at eHealth NSW, you will be part of a cross functional team of digital healthcare specialists, corporate product, data & intelligence analytics and technology professionals; creating and continuously improving an analytics product suite aimed at improving value-based care delivery within a psychologically safe, inclusive, accountable and high-performance culture.

About us

The Australian Institute of Company Directors (AICD) is committed to strengthening society through world-class governance. We aim to be the independent and trusted voice of governance, building the capability of a community of leaders for the benefit of society. Our membership of more than 53,000 includes directors and senior leaders from business, government and the not-for-profit sectors. 




About the team

The CRM team sits within the Customer Service and Technology function and is responsible for the delivery of CRM improvements and enhancements that drive operational efficiencies, user adoption and an enhanced customer experience
 

About the role

As an Analyst, you’ll play a key role in shaping and delivering the CRM that enhances the experience of AICD members and clients. Working at the intersection of business, technology and user experience, you’ll ensure real‑world needs and insights are embedded into the design and delivery of digital products and platforms.

Your remit will be broad and will include:

Partner with key stakeholders and user groups to identify, capture, validate and analyse business and user requirements across digital products and platforms.
Ensure requirements are clear, complete, consistent and feasible, adhering to organisational standards and templates.
Develop high‑quality functional and non‑functional specifications, including system designs, process models, diagrams and supporting documentation.
Translate requirements into well‑defined epics and user stories that accurately reflect user needs and product functionality.
Continually review and refine requirements, identifying issues or gaps and providing clear, timely reporting.
Support the deployment of new digital products and enhancements to existing platforms.
Assist with the development of test plans, performance measures and user‑acceptance activities to ensure solutions meet agreed requirements.
Contribute to the ongoing adoption and improvement of Agile practices across the full product lifecycle, with a strong focus on delivering value.
Stay across emerging digital, software and hardware trends, contributing ideas to improve solutions and optimise development processes.
Conduct cost‑benefit analysis to support informed decision‑making around proposed systems and enhancements.



About you

You will have strong technical aptitude and previous relevant experience, and you will champion the AICD values of: Accountability, Respect, Excellence and Collaboration. In addition, you will also have the following:

Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Computer Science or similar related experience. 
Agile Certified, or with proven experience in an Agile project management environment. 
Minimum 4 years of experience in a similar business and technical requirements analysis position. 
Extensive experience using Microsoft Excel, Microsoft PowerPoint, Microsoft Access, SQL, Google Analytics and Tableau. 
Extensive experience contributing to the design development and implementation of software solutions, systems or products. 
Extensive experience creating systematic and consistent requirements specifications in both technical and user-friendly language. 
Extensive experience applying analytical and statistical skills to systems issues and products. 
Extensive experience working within Agile environments with a heavy emphasis on user stories and acceptance criteria through to deployment.

Join Us!

At AICD, you’ll join a purpose‑driven organisation that empowers leaders and strengthens Australia’s governance landscape. You’ll work with a collaborative, supportive team that values innovation, curiosity, and continuous improvement. Your expertise will have a visible impact across the marketing team and the organisation. 

Enjoy true flexibility with hybrid working arrangements that support balance and productivity.

Alinta Energy is one of Australia’s biggest energy retailers, generators and developers with over 1.1 million customers. Australia’s energy system is undergoing the biggest transformation in its history and we’re right there with it. We’re investing in and developing large-scale renewables and storage projects as part of our ongoing effort to provide our customers with reliable, affordable and sustainable energy.

We understand that flexibility matters when considering your next role. Let us know your requirements, and we’ll carefully consider how we might accommodate them.

Ready to make a real impact?

Alinta Energy is hiring a dedicated Small Business Pricing Strategy Analyst to accelerate growth in our small business customer segment. This role sits at the intersection of pricing development, commercial analysis and system enablement, with a strong initial focus on helping design and establish the new system functionality and processes needed to support a deeper and more tailored approach to small business pricing. Reporting directly to the Head of Pricing, you’ll shape pricing direction for this segment, guide how pricing is delivered through our systems, and operate with a high level of autonomy in a role that plays a foundational part in how we grow and compete in the small business market. You’ll turn complex cost, customer and regulatory inputs into clear, commercially sound pricing outcomes, while partnering closely with teams across Sales, Product, Customer Strategy, Wholesale and Billing to drive effective execution.

Why you’ll love working here

At Alinta Energy, we’re taking real action to deliver reliable and sustainable energy for Australia — and that practical approach runs through everything we do. You’ll get clear direction, genuine flexibility, and the support you need to grow, all while working on projects that make a lasting difference. We’re big enough to create impact, but small enough that your ideas and effort will always be seen.

There are plenty of other great benefits of working for Alinta Energy, including flexible working, energy discounts, an Employee Assistance Program (EAP), a paid volunteer day each year, fully stocked kitchens, and lots more.

What you'll do

Design and guide system and process changes that enable more real-time, targeted and segment-specific small business pricing
Analyse, design and implement timely, customer-focused small business pricing strategies grounded in competitive, regulatory, commercial and financial drivers
Build, refine and maintain pricing tools, financial models and reporting that support insight generation and help identify opportunities to further improve small business pricing.
Work proactively and independently, setting clear priorities, communicating progress confidently, and driving continuous improvement across pricing, systems and processes
Lead process and control improvements for small business pricing, including documentation and support for system updates and new capabilities.
Collaborate across Wholesale, Product, Customer Strategy, Sales, Billing and network stakeholders to build insights, validate assumptions and drive better commercial decisions.

Your experience

Strong quantitative and financial modelling capability, ideally with a degree in commerce, economics, accounting, maths or similar
Proven analytical ability and commercial acumen - able to translate complex cost, regulatory and competitive factors into pricing recommendations.
Excellent communication skills, capable of simplifying complexity for senior leaders, technical teams and cross-functional stakeholders.
Experience working autonomously in environments that require process creation, system understanding and structured methodical execution.
Strong problem solving capability, with the ability to navigate ambiguity, work through incomplete information, and develop practical, commercially sound solutions
Energy retail or SME-segment experience (pricing, billing, settlements or product) highly desirable but not essential if you bring the right quantitative skills

Please note this role requires full working rights within Australia.

Public Skills Australia has been appointed by the Department of Employment and Workplace Relations (DEWR) as one of 10 Jobs and Skills Councils. We work with employer and employee representatives from the Public Safety and Government industry-sectors – Police, Fire and Emergency Services, Correctional Services, Defence, and all levels of Government – to ensure Australia’s vocational education and training (VET) system delivers better outcomes for learners and employers. A primary function of our work is to provide workforce planning, industry intelligence and training product development in support of industry needs and government priorities.

The Manager Workforce Planning and Insights is accountable to the Director Workforce Strategy and Insights and delivers the Public Skills Australia’s Workforce Planning and Research functions. The Manager Workforce Planning and Insights is part of the management team and will oversee the day-to-day management of the Workforce Planning and Insights team. This position will be accountable for the end-to-end planning, management and delivery of successful projects, including reporting, monitoring, and tracking deliverables and milestones and managing budgets and associated risks. While this position reports to the Director they may be required to report to other executive staff depending on the projects they need to manage.

Workforce Planning: This role will lead the development and delivery of annual Workforce Insights Reports by managing a small team of staff dedicated to these deliverables. The delivery of the Workforce Insights Reports required robust desktop and applied research, quantitative analysis of national and industry datasets, qualitative research methods to draw out industry insights and comprehensive consultation of data and findings. The Manager, Workforce Planning and Insights will be responsible for the overarching team planning and project planning to ensure all milestones are met. The Workforce Planning function also requires comprehensive written capability to draft and review extensive reports.

Research: The Manager Workforce Planning and Insights will also oversee a small team of staff dedicated to producing individual research projects that give effect to workforce strategies, ministerial priorities, industry sector requirements and Board directives. This position will oversee the management of a range of project involving analysis of qualitative and quantitative data to deliver research and other project deliverables. They will lead a small team, develop a workplan to deliver projects on the annual Public Skills Australia Business Plan, manage and contract subcontractors, manage their budget and ensure robust consultation, good governance and adherence to federal government requirements.

Responsibilities

In partnership with internal stakeholders and external service providers, with the intent of ensuring compliance with relevant legislative, grant and company compliance obligations, the Manager Workforce Planning and Insights will:

• Manage the Workforce Planning and Insights team, including HR activities (probations, performance reviews, professional development, WHS and other requirements) and ensure appropriate professional behaviour in line with the company values.

• Develop and deliver the annual business plan for the team, meeting quality, governance and consultation expectations and processes.

• Oversee the development and completion of high-quality reports, plans by leading research, data analysis and the development of insights and findings that meets the expectations of their executive.

• Undertake thorough industry consultation through various engagement and research methods, including workshop facilitation.

• Maintain productive relationships with internal and external stakeholders, often at a senior and executive level demonstrating strong political acumen and corporate maturity.

• Manage and contribute to relevant stakeholder networks and/or governance groups (as determined by business need) by supporting the Chair, engaging with members of the group and contributing to all aspects of their meetings and meeting preparation.

• Undertake end-to-end project management of Workforce Insights Reports and Research deliverables, by scoping, planning, managing, and monitoring project plans.

• Manage budgets, ensuring good fiscal practice and risks are proactively identified and mitigated.

• Undertake procurement processes and manage subcontractors to support the delivery of individual research projects and other business plan items.

• Manage a team, including probations, performance and other human resource requirements.

• Proactively brief their Director and Executive on the progress of projects, along with any opportunities, challenges, risks and solutions.

• Present to a variety of audiences (including executives) using excellent written and verbal communication skills.

• Work collaboratively with other areas of the business, relevant Managers and other members of staff.

• Any other reasonable duties as required.

Key Selection Criteria – Essential

• Demonstrated experience leading and managing teams and subcontractors in a complex, changing, and busy environment to deliver successful outcomes whilst exhibiting professional behaviour in line with organisational values. 

• Ability to develop and motivate staff and develop a high-performance culture.

• A Higher Education qualification such as a relevant Bachelor’s or Master’s degree.

• Experience with complex research methodologies and policy skills at a senior level in an applied setting.

• Excellent written and verbal communications skills.

• Demonstrated capability to negotiate and build consensus with internal and external stakeholders.

• Proven ability to facilitate workshops and deliver engaging presentations.

• Operate with a high level of political acumen and corporate maturity to build relationship with senior and executive level stakeholders.

• Experience in project management, planning and budgetary practices.

• Ability to manage contracts, using established procurement processes.

• Motivated to drive a positive can-do culture across the company.

• Proven capability work on multiple products in a fast-paced environment.

• Strong interpersonal skills, with a motivation and preparedness to support the Executive of the organisation.

Key Selection Criteria – Desirable

• Experience working within the Public Safety and Government industry sectors.

• Experience in workforce planning, policy development AND/OR strategic foresight AND/OR environmental scanning.

How to apply

Your application must include a CV/Resume of no more than 4 pages and a Cover Letter of no more than 2 pages. The Cover Letter should not repeat information contained in the CV but specifically address the ‘essential’ Key Selection Criteria. Any queries should be directed to the HR Team at careers@publicskillsaustralia.org.au. Applications close at midnight, Monday 9 February 2026.

Applications will be processed as they are received, interviews and appointment may occur before the end date.
